Freddie Gray was arrested on April 12 in Baltimore and died a week later from a severe spinal injury . 
  Gray was not strapped into a seat belt when he was taken to the police station in a paddy wagon . 
  Baltimore police rules say all detainees must be strapped in by seat belts or other restraining devices  . 
  Gray family lawyer said his spine was ' 80 per cent severed at his neck' in police custody . 
  Police union lawyer said Gray was handcuffed and put in leg irons but not strapped in . 
  Gray died on April 19 . 
 